🔹 Introduction to C Programming
C Programming Language is a powerful, general-purpose language created by Dennis Ritchie at Bell Labs in 1972. It is widely regarded as the foundation of modern programming because many popular languages such as C++, Java, and Python are built on its concepts.

✨ Key Features
-> Structured → supports modular programming with functions

-> Efficient → produces fast, optimized machine-level code

-> Portable → runs across different platforms with minimal changes

-> Low-level access → allows direct memory manipulation using pointers

-> Rich libraries → provides built-in functions for I/O, strings, and math

📌 Why Learn C?
-> Builds strong fundamentals in programming and computer science

-> Essential for system programming, operating systems, compilers, and embedded systems

-> Helps in understanding how computers work internally

-> Forms the base for learning advanced languages

🚀 Applications
-> Operating systems (e.g., UNIX, Linux kernel)

-> Compilers and interpreters

-> Embedded systems and microcontrollers

-> Game development

-> Database systems